1.11 Part j
Create a function called evaluate.row(...) that takes one argument and returns “low” when the argument is less than 4, “mid” when the argument is between 4 and 7 (inclusive), and “high” when the arguement is 8 or larger. Then, use sapply(...) to apply it to column x1.
Solution:
Used if-statements in the evaluate.row function to determine is a number is “high”, “low”, or “mid”



Code
evaluate.row&lt;-function(dat){
  if(dat&lt;4){
    return("low")
  }else if(dat&gt;=4 && dat&lt;=7){
    return("mid")
  }else if(dat&gt;=8){
    return("high")
  }
}
df$category &lt;- sapply(df$x1, evaluate.row)
(df$category)


